This completes the proof of the lemma for the case where $c$ is a 5-cycle. Now suppose that $c$ is a 7-cycle.
We start again from the edge $wu$. Fixing one of the domains labelled $2$ for $w$, there are, up to reflection, four choices of a domain labelled $1$ for $u$, as shown in the two drawings in Figure~\ref{figure:wu}. For each of the two choices for $u$ on the left in Figure~\ref{figure:wu}, edge removal may be performed on one of two edges drawn in bold; one chooses an edge that is not incident to $v$. This reduces the length of $c$ to five. For the two choices for $u$ on the right in Figure~\ref{figure:wu}, edge removal may not be possible, depending on which vertex of ${\mathcal{T}}(c)$ is $v$. It remains to treat these two possibilities.

